<TITLE> HC asks why UP boundaries should not be redrawn </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 16 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Tuesday asked the government and the Election Commission to explain why union parishads across the country should not be re-demarcated in line with voter population. Mahbubur Rahman Tulu, president of Bangladesh Union Parishad Forum, filed the petition with the High Court bench comprising justices AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury and Borhanuddin. The petitioner sought a court order for redrawing the boundaries, in accordance with voter spread, ahead of the next union parishad elections. There are 4498 union parishads, representing the lowest strata of local government. Elections to the councils are due this year. The bench set Feb 23 for the next hearing on the petition. b
